A gem in the Bronx.  Very much a no frills, hole-in-the-wall traditional Jamaican restaurant. The owners are Jamaican and so was the clientele, which check two boxes on my authentic food meter. The service itself was a bit brusque, but remember you're not there to be wowed by customer service.  It took me awhile to decide between the jerk chicken and the oxtail; I eventually went with the chicken and was very happy with my choice. The serving was huge and it was the best jerk chicken I've had in NYC. Highly recommend. Can't wait to go back to try the oxtail.

The service is horrible. So one night I started craving oxtails. So I head over to this place. I'm new around the area and definitely to the restaurant. As my friend and I take our time to look on their menu the older lady says " you need to hurry up and order because we are about to close". So I just went ahead and ordered as my friend was still  unsure. I asked " do you guys sale stew or jerk chicken on the side" the lady says " no , you just have to buy the whole thing. Hurry up and make up your mind we soon close." I didn't understand why this lady was so mean and rude to me. I then asked about their Mac and cheese. Long story short. She became even more mean and nasty with me. Telling me to make up my mind. She tells me that I'm making a problem for her business because I don't know what I want. I'm still calm at this point and explained to her it's new to me. Apart of me wants to try a little of everything. She just kept going on. So I asked for my money back because she has just been rude and mean to me the whole time there. She tells me no. And locks her cashier draw. After arguing her down and talking to the other staff. They told her to give me my money back. This lady had the nerve to throw the money back in my face. Literally touching my face. Now as pregnant as I am my head damn near blew off from  rage. I'm arguing with her about what she just did and she picks something up to hit me. I've never ever experienced something so crazy in my life. After leaving there I kept saying why was she so mad at me? Really unprofessional, unpleasant, & definitely  dysfunctional business.
